cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SY. 

The paper focuses on a robot arm learning to pick and throw objects through trial and error using visual observations, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The use of visual observations suggests a focus on computer vision (cs.CV) techniques. The end-to-end formulation and use of deep learning also suggest a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the investigation of synergies between grasping and throwing and the use of a physics simulator suggest a focus on systems and control (cs.SY).
